  "text": "The motivation for this experiment was to check whether it is possible to prepare a classifier with CNN, which enables correct recognition between cell boundary and cell center. The input image resolution was set to 64×64, which size was motivated by previous research concerning this problem conducted in [CITATION_1] . The network was trained through 20 epochs with the learning rate set to 0.01 and mini-batch capacity of 64. The dataset consisted of around 20,000 of images, where 90% were used for training and 10% constituted a validation set. The backpropagation method used stochastic gradient descent.",
